<Requirements version="1" hierarchy="LLR">
  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.1 Explore Maze -->
  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration State Machine</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a top-level exploration state machine with at least the states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED} and deterministic transitions between them, such that in the EXPLORE state the robot autonomously explores the unknown maze until a stop condition is met.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Start Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enter the EXPLORE state automatically on system startup after completion of all initialization routines and successful acquisition of at least one valid set of sensor measurements.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Stop Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall terminate the EXPLORE state and initiate RETURN_TO_START when the internal map contains a classification (free or blocked) for every cell and inter-cell wall location of the 4x8 maze grid, or when the global exploration time limit of 5 minutes is reached, whichever occurs first.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier-Based Exploration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-based exploration strategy in the EXPLORE state, selecting as navigation targets cells that are currently classified as unknown but are adjacent (in the 4-neighborhood) to at least one free cell in the internal map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Target Selection Heuristic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall prioritize exploration frontier targets using a heuristic that minimizes an estimate of travel time (e.g., shortest path length in cells) from the current cell to the frontier while preferring frontiers that increase the number of newly observable cells, in order to reduce overall exploration time within the 5 minute limit.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.2 Wall Detection -->
  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Front Wall Detection From Ultrasonic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret a front ultrasonic distance measurement as a front wall in the current maze cell if, after accounting for ±12 cm sensor accuracy, the measured distance range overlaps the expected distance from the robot center to a cell boundary wall based on the 17.2 cm cell size and 11 cm robot diameter.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Side Wall Detection From IR</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret an active obstacle indication from a left or right infrared sensor as a wall located along the corresponding side of the current maze cell if the robot’s pose is aligned to the maze axes within a configurable angular tolerance not exceeding 10 degrees.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Proximity Thresholding</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall apply configurable numeric thresholds and hysteresis to raw ultrasonic distance measurements to distinguish between free space and wall presence, such that single-sample noise or transient spikes do not cause flip-flopping between wall and free classifications.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Avoidance Maneuvers</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall command motor speeds to execute avoidance maneuvers (e.g., stop and turn, or arc turns) when front or side wall detections indicate that the predicted robot trajectory would intersect a wall within one cell length, thereby preventing collisions while maintaining progress toward exploration or path-planning goals.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.3 Create Map -->
  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Data Structure</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an in-memory grid map data structure representing the 4x8 maze, where each cell and each inter-cell wall segment is explicitly stored with its classification and can be addressed by integer coordinates (row, column) aligned with the assumed physical maze geometry.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell and Wall Update From Sensors</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall update the grid map cells and wall segments based on processed ultrasonic and infrared measurements obtained while the robot is located in a cell center or during cell transitions, marking corresponding walls as blocked or free and updating adjacent cells as free if traversed without collision.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Unknown Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initialize all cells and wall segments in the 4x8 grid map to an unknown classification at system startup prior to any sensor-based observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Start Cell Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall designate a fixed coordinate in the grid map as the start cell at initialization, set its classification to free, and maintain a record of this coordinate for use in return-to-start and second-run behaviors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-1.3.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Static Map Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
